  "prompt": "How much does an Olympic gold medal cost?",
  "response": "The value of an Olympic gold medal varies depending on the specific Games and the current market prices of metals. However, here are some general details:\n\n1. Material composition:\n- Modern Olympic gold medals are not made of solid gold\n- They are primarily made of silver, with a gold plating\n- They are typically about 92.5% silver and at least 6 grams of gold\n\n2. Approximate material value:\n- The raw material value is usually around $500-$800\n- In the 2016 Rio Olympics, the medal's material value was estimated at about $565\n\n3. Actual market value:\n- Collectible gold medals from famous athletes can sell for much more\n- Prices can range from thousands to hundreds of thousands of dollars, depending on the athlete and historical significance\n\n4. Cost to produce:\n- The actual cost of manufacturing an Olympic medal is typically around $500-$700\n\nThe exact value can fluctuate based on current metal prices and the specific Games. The sentimental and historical value of an Olympic gold medal far exceeds its material worth.",
